Championship Final

[between winners first and second stage]

First Leg
[Jun 6]
Bahia      2-0  Vitória

Second Leg
[Jun 13]
Vitória    n/p Bahia

[Vitória had a home leg, at Barradão Stadium, but Bahia won at
 the sports court the right to play at its stadium, Fonte Nova. 
 At the day of the game, each team went to a different stadium 
 and both teams celebrated the title by w/o.]

[In December 2002, the Bahia FA declared this championship as with no winners.]

[In January 2005, the Bahia FA decides to share the title. So, Bahia and Vitoria
are Bahia State Champions 1999] 

[Bahia FA declared Poções as 1999 runner-up] 


Top Scorer: Dejan Petkovic (Vitória) with 18 goals.

Relegation Playoff

First Leg
Fluminense      1-1  Galícia

Second Leg
Galícia         0-0  Fluminense         3-5 pen

Fluminense promoted to First Level, Galícia relegated to Second Level.     


